com.vernalis.pdbconnector2.dialogcomponents

Class DialogComponentStringArrayInput

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.defaultnodesettings.DialogComponent
      • com.vernalis.pdbconnector2.dialogcomponents.DialogComponentStringArrayInput

  • public class DialogComponentStringArrayInput
extends org.knime.core.node.defaultnodesettings.DialogComponent
    A DialogComponent to allow the input of an array of Strings. The input can be free text, via a Suggester, or as a JComboBox dropdown depending on the constructor used. The component is displayed as a table with the inputs in the first column and columns showing '+' or 'X' (add or delete input) columns and a column with a logic operator (AND or OR)
    Since:
    1.28.0
    Author:
    S.Roughley knime@vernalis.com
